Create a new nextjs application using "npx create-next-app";
npm install --leagcy-peer-deps // used to instal already defined 
dependencies in the package.json.

for fetching data in NextJs you use the getServerSideProps funtion
 ctrl +  shift + r to trigger a hard reload and cache clearing in the browser

slug: is a unique identifier that belongs to each products.

React context: a single source of data for managing the application

Number one rule in react never mutate the state using the = symbol.
.splice method is a mutative method(its mutates the state)
.filter does not mutate the state.


